[3] Saudi Arabia: surveillance, Ministry of Public Health
Date: Fri 24 May 2013
Source: Saudi Arabia Ministry of Public Health [edited]
http://www.moh.gov.sa/en/Ministry/MediaCenter/News/Pages/News-2013-05-24-002.aspx


MOH statement related to the updates of the novel coronavirus infection -- 24 May
-------------------------------------------------------------
The Ministry of Health (MOH) has announced that no new confirmed Coronavirus cases have been recorded since the last statement 2 days ago. Within the framework of the constant monitoring and the epidemiological surveillance of the competent committees, the MOH has pointed out that 146 suspected samples have been laboratory analyzed during that period; where results proved negative.

Within the same vein, the MOH has expounded that the national scientific committees keep on holding its meetings in the ministry's headquarter to follow up the latest developments about this virus, and they will keep everyone abreast with the updates in this regard.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[From the Ministry of Public Health Press release above it is clear that there is active surveillance for the MERS-CoV ongoing in Saudi Arabia, with 146 suspected cases tested for the virus in a 48 hour period, all with negative results. - Mod.MPP]

